8 HOUSE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 164,
9 L.D. 261, “An Act Regarding the Authority of Municipalities to Regulate Timber
10 Harvesting”
11 Amend the amendment by inserting after the title the following:
12 'Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1.'
13 Amend the amendment by striking out all of the 2nd instructional paragraph (page 1,
14 lines 13 to 15 in amendment) and inserting the following:
15 'Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 by striking out all of paragraph E-1 (page
16 2, lines 42 to 44 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
17 'E-1. A municipal timber harvesting ordinance adopted after January 1, 2026 takes
18 effect only after certification by the bureau that the municipality adopted the timber
19 harvesting ordinance in accordance with the process requirements of this subsection.' '
20 Amend the amendment by striking out all of the 4th instructional paragraph (page 1,
21 lines 18 to 20 in amendment).
22 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
23 section number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment amends Committee Amendment "A" to remove from the bill the
2266 change to the definition of "timber harvesting activities." It allows timber harvesting
2277 ordinances adopted after January 1, 2026 to take effect only after certification by the
2288 Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, Bureau of Forestry. It also removes
2299 from the committee amendment an instruction to change the process for the clerk of a
3300 municipality to notify the bureau of a timber harvesting ordinance.
